  <ul>
    <li>
      <b>Core Proficiencies:</b> JavaScript (ES6+), TypeScript, Vue.js, Nuxt, Tailwind
      CSS, HTML5, CSS3/SCSS, Python, Django.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Platform & Infrastructure:</b> Storyblok CMS, PrimeVue, AWS, REST APIs, Git/GitHub.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Development Standards:</b> Responsive Design, Web Accessibility (a11y), Technical
      Documentation, Component-Driven Architecture.
    </li>
    <li>
      <b>Current Focus & Implementation:</b> React, Next.js, Astro, AI-Assisted Development
      (Claude Code, Gemini).
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="pt-3">PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE</h3>

  <h4 class="mb-0">
    Senior Software Engineer &ndash; EnergySage &ndash; Boston, MA
  </h4>
  <p class="mb-1"><i>October 2012 &ndash; June 2025</i></p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      Architected and maintained scalable Vue.js components using
      JavaScript/TypeScript and an internal design system, improving UI
      consistency and developer efficiency.
    </li>
    <li>
      Integrated Storyblok CMS to empower non-technical stakeholders to
      independently update content, significantly reducing engineering support
      requests.
    </li>
    <li>
      Standardized styling across legacy and modern codebases by consolidating
      Bootstrap and CSS patterns, reducing UI drift and simplifying maintenance.
    </li>
    <li>
      Authored technical documentation for architectural decisions and frontend
      services to streamline onboarding and cross-team knowledge sharing.
    </li>
    <li>
      Mentored junior developers through code reviews and pair programming,
      accelerating their progression to independent contributors.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h4 class="mb-0">Web Developer &ndash; Verndale &ndash; Boston, MA</h4>
  <p class="mb-1"><i>April 2012 &ndash; October 2012</i></p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      Developed responsive, accessible website templates from design comps and
      interaction specs.
    </li>
    <li>
      Collaborated with QA to ensure cross-browser compatibility and reliable
      user experiences.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="pt-3">EDUCATION</h3>

  <h4>
    Bachelor of Science, Computer Science &ndash; University of Massachusetts
    Dartmouth
